'''''Superbike Challenge''''' is a 1987 video game published by [[Broderbund]] and developed by [[MC2-Microids]].

==Gameplay==
''Superbike Challenge'' is a game in which 12 courses (including Bugatti, Misano, Salzburgring, and Silverstone) are featured, with three difficulty levels.<ref name="CGW46"/>

==Reception==
David M. Wilson and Johnny L. Wilson reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "If you would rather race over authentic courses, Broderbund's Superbike Challenge [...] features 12 authentic courses".<ref name="CGW46">{{cite magazine |last1=Wilson |first1=David M. |last2=Wilson |first2=Johnny L. |title=The Boys of Spring: A Computer Sports Survey |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=April 1988 |volume=1 |issue=46 |pages=14}}</ref>

